Download Haar Cascade Frontal Face:

Go to the OpenCV website: https://opencv.org/
https://github.com/opencv/opencv/blob/master/data/haarcascades/haarcascade_frontalface_default.xml
Click on the "Download" tab in the top menu bar
Select the appropriate version of OpenCV for your operating system and download it
Once downloaded, extract the files to a location on your computer
Copy and paste your face tracking code:

Open a new Python file in your preferred editor
Copy and paste your face tracking code into the new file
Save the file with a meaningful name
Download PySerial:

Go to the PySerial website: https://pyserial.readthedocs.io/en/latest/pyserial.html
Click on the "Installation" tab in the left-hand menu
Follow the installation instructions for your operating system
Once installed, you should be able to import the PySerial module in your Python code
Copy and paste your Arduino code:

Open the Arduino IDE
Copy and paste your Arduino code into a new sketch
Save the sketch with a meaningful name
Connect two servos to pin 5,6:

Connect the ground pin of each servo to a ground pin on the Arduino
Connect the power pin of each servo to a 5V pin on the Arduino
Connect the signal pin of the first servo to pin 5 on the Arduino
Connect the signal pin of the second servo to pin 6 on the Arduino
Enjoy your face tracking project:

Upload the Arduino sketch to the Arduino board
Run your Python code and enjoy watching your servos track your face!
